title: Study of the levels of 77,79,81,83Br with the 76,78,80,82Se(3He,d) reaction.

x4freetext: Study of the levels of 77,79,81,83Br with the
76,78,80,82Se(3He,d) reaction.

x4freetext: Reaction products were analysed with the 100 cm
magnetic spectrograph.
The targets were prepared by vacuum evaporation of 75
to 100 mu-g/cm2 of Se metal onto a 10 mu-g/cm2 carbon
foil. The targets were covered with approximately 50
mu-g/cm2 of gold. This left the Se sandwiched between
layers of gold and carbon.

x4freetext: At each spectrograph angle 3He`s were recorded
with a silicon surface barrier detector fixed at angle
equal 60 degr. in the scattering chamber.
The yield of the 3He`s to the first excited state in
the Se target isotope was used to normalize the
angular distribution from angle to angle.
A target isotopically enriched to 99.45%  was used.

x4freetext: Deuterons were detected with position
sensitive gas proportional counters (PC) mounted on
the spectrograph focal surface.
The nuclear track plates used for the
excitation energy measurements were also used for the
angular distributions. The track-plate data in general
had slightly better resolution (18-25 keV FWHM) than
the PC data which had 25-30kev FWHM resolution.
Absolute differential cross sections for the
76Se(3He,d)77Br reactions were measured at
a laboratory scattering angle of 30 degr. by
simultaneously recording events from the (3He,d)
reaction and from elastic scattering. After correcting
the reaction yield and elastic yield for differences in
the spectrograph solid angle, the absolute reaction
cross sections were determined from the elastic
scattering cross sections and the ratio of the reaction
yield to the elastic yield.
A target isotopically enriched to 96.88% was used.

x4freetext: Deuterons were detected with position
sensitive gas proportional counters (PC) mounted on
the spectrograph focal surface.
The nuclear track plates used for the
excitation energy measurements were also used for the
angular distributions. The track-plate data in general
had slightly better resolution (18-25 keV FWHM) than
the PC data which had 25-30kev FWHM resolution.
The 82Se(3He,d)83Br absolute cross sections were
determined using the 79,81Br isotopic contaminant
groups in the 83Br deuteron spectra and the relative
abundances of the 78,80,82Se isotopes in the 82Se
target.
A target isotopically enriched to 87.8% was used.
